    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning kinda yellow and pale compared to the top ones. what's probably going on with them?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The yellowing leaves on the lower part of your tomato plants are likely due to a decrease in light intensity as the plant grows taller. As the plant reaches for the sun, it can create a \"shade zone\" around itself, where the lower leaves are less exposed to direct sunlight. This can cause a reduction in chlorophyll production, leading to the yellowing of the lower leaves. It's a common issue, and you can try pruning the lower leaves to improve air circulation and prevent fungal diseases.",
