    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the tips. i think i'll try some sulfur to bring the ph down. it honestly just feels like something is eating away at the plant's energy/nutrients before they can even get to the top. like the soil is being hollowed out or something. is that normal for nitrogen issues, or is there something else that could be stripping the nutrients away so fast?",
